==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Frothy
<hw>Froth"y</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <amorph>[<pos>Compar.</pos>
<adjf>Frothier</adjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>superl.</pos>
<adjf>Frothiest</adjf>.]</amorph> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Full of foam or
froth, or consisting of froth or light bubbles; spumous;
foamy.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Not firm or solid; soft; unstable.</def>
<rj><au>Bacon.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Of the nature of froth; light; empty; unsubstantial;
<as>as, a <ex>frothy</ex> speaker or harangue</as>.</def>
<rj><au>Tillotson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Froufrou</ent>⟦br⟧
\'d8
